- All operations (`get`, `put`, `size`, and `clear`) are thread-safe by using a `std::mutex`.
- The code handles the case when capacity is 0 properly by preventing any inserts.
- The eviction logic correctly checks for `>=` instead of `>` to maintain the right capacity. 

